The paper discusses the use of reactive answer set programming for incorporating online information into solving processes, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of this technology in dynamic environments, such as assisted living and cognitive robotics, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the incorporation of facts, rules, or queries provided by a user, which is a common topic in databases (cs.DB) and programming languages (cs.PL).
